-- Australia shares, defying commodities rout & weak GDP, close higher
-- 
-- Wed Dec 03, 2014 12:22AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 3 (Reuters) - Australian shares rose 0.8 percent on Wednesday as investors shrugged off disappointing economic data and further declines in oil and iron ore prices and bought stocks on the cheap after the recent steep selloff. [ID:nL3N0TN16K]

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> extended the previous session's recovery after plunging nearly 4 percent in two sessions. The benchmark closed up 40.5 points at 5,321.8, pulling away from a two-month low touched this week.